    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-11-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-04-27T21:01:37Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from the gross income of certain banks interest received on small business loans of up to $5 million. </p> <p>The bill applies to loans that are: (1) secured by land situated in the United States that is used or held by the small business in connection with the active conduct of a farming business, or (2) incurred in the ordinary course of the trade or business of the small business. </p> <p>To be eligible for the exclusion, the bank must: (1) have less than $50 billion in assets at the closing of the preceding taxable year, and (2) receive the interest before 2019. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to provide an exclusion from gross income for interest on certain small business loans.</title>
